&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Lab Technician to join our team. This role will report to a Manager within the R&amp;amp;D organization. This position will support various R&amp;amp;D projects through laboratory operations, sample preparation, equipment maintenance, and testing activities. The Lab Technician will work closely with operators on fuel sample processing and assist with catalyst preparation and reactor operation under the direction of scientists and engineers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Lab Technician will be responsible for executing laboratory procedures, preparing samples, maintaining equipment, recording data, and supporting safe and efficient laboratory operations. This role is based in person, 5 days a week in New Britain, PA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you get to do&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with catalyst preparation and reactor setup, operation, and shutdown activities following established procedures and under the guidance of scientists and engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare samples and perform laboratory testing using established methods and procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain laboratory equipment and ensure instruments are clean, calibrated, and operating properly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record experimental observations, test results, and laboratory data accurately and in a timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow laboratory protocols, standard operating procedures, and safety guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean, organized, and safe laboratory environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with troubleshooting equipment issues and escalate concerns to scientists, engineers, or senior technical staff as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with inventory management, ordering supplies, and maintaining stock levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support assembly, cleaning, maintenance, and preparation of laboratory and pilot-scale equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with scientists, engineers, operators, and other team members to support laboratory operations and project objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate&#39;s degree in Chemistry, Chemical Engineering Technology, Engineering Technology, or a related technical field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous laboratory experience preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of chemical principles and laboratory techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
